<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.0.0">Jekyll</generator><link href="http://localhost:4000/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="http://localhost:4000/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2021-06-01T22:26:24+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Quốc Khải Blog</title><subtitle>While the world sleeps, I dream</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Text to speech using AVSpeechSynthesizer</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/text-to-speech-using-AVSpeechSynthesizer/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Text to speech using AVSpeechSynthesizer" /><published>2021-01-25T00:00:00+07:00</published><updated>2021-01-25T00:00:00+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/text-to-speech-using-AVSpeechSynthesizer</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/text-to-speech-using-AVSpeechSynthesizer/">&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;AVSpeechSynthesizer&lt;/code&gt; to convert text to speech in easy way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, import &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;AVFoundation&lt;/code&gt; to your class:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-swift highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;kd&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kt&quot;&gt;AVFoundation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Create and using &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;AVSpeechSynthesizer&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-swift highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;utterance&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kt&quot;&gt;AVSpeechUtterance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;Hello world&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;utterance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;voice&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kt&quot;&gt;AVSpeechSynthesisVoice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;language&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;en-GB&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;utterance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rate&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mf&quot;&gt;0.5&lt;/span&gt; 

&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;synthesizer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kt&quot;&gt;AVSpeechSynthesizer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;synthesizer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;speak&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;utterance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can custom &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;AVSpeechSynthesisVoice&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;language&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;identifier&lt;/code&gt; (ex: &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;com.apple.ttsbundle.Samantha-compact&lt;/code&gt; for Samantha voice).&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="iOS" /><category term="speech" /><summary type="html">Using AVSpeechSynthesizer to convert text to speech in easy way.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Animating A Sequence of Images</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/animating-a-sequence-of-images/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Animating A Sequence of Images" /><published>2020-12-15T00:00:00+07:00</published><updated>2020-12-15T00:00:00+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/animating-a-sequence-of-images</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/animating-a-sequence-of-images/">&lt;p&gt;You can create a repeating “flip book” or animated gif effect given multiple images.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;images&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;duration&lt;/code&gt; like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-swift highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;imageView&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;image&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kt&quot;&gt;UIImage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;animatedImage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;with&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;images&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;duration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mf&quot;&gt;2.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-swift highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;imageView&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;animationImages&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;images&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;imageView&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;animationDuration&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mf&quot;&gt;2.0&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;imageView&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;startAnimating&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="iOS" /><category term="animation" /><summary type="html">You can create a repeating “flip book” or animated gif effect given multiple images.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">How to copy text to the clipboard using UIPasteboard</title><link href="http://localhost:4000/how-to-copy-text-to-the-clipboard-using-UIPasteboard/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to copy text to the clipboard using UIPasteboard" /><published>2020-05-28T00:00:00+07:00</published><updated>2020-05-28T00:00:00+07:00</updated><id>http://localhost:4000/how-to-copy-text-to-the-clipboard-using-UIPasteboard</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://localhost:4000/how-to-copy-text-to-the-clipboard-using-UIPasteboard/">&lt;p&gt;You can write to and read from the iOS clipboard by using the &lt;strong&gt;UIPasteboard&lt;/strong&gt; class, which has a &lt;strong&gt;generalPasteboard()&lt;/strong&gt; method that returns the shared system method of copying and pasting data between apps. Using this you can write text to the clipboard just like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-swift highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;pasteboard&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;kt&quot;&gt;UIPasteboard&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;general&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;pasteboard&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;Hello, world!&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To read text back from the clipboard, you should unwrap its optional value like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;language-swift highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;pasteboard&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;// text was found and placed in the &quot;string&quot; constant&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="iOS" /><summary type="html">You can write to and read from the iOS clipboard by using the UIPasteboard class, which has a generalPasteboard() method that returns the shared system method of copying and pasting data between apps. Using this you can write text to the clipboard just like this:</summary></entry></feed>